The urban fluxes module has already been fully ported and committed (commit `27b7717`). Here's a summary of what's in place:

**`src/biogeophys/urban_fluxes.jl`** — Complete port of `UrbanFluxesMod.F90` containing:
- `UrbanFluxesParamsData` struct + `urban_fluxes_read_params!()` — module-level parameters
- `simple_wasteheatfromac()` — waste heat from AC (simple CLM4.5 method)
- `wasteheat!()` — total waste heat from urban heating/cooling
- `calc_simple_internal_building_temp!()` — internal building temperature (simple method)
- `urban_fluxes!()` — main subroutine: turbulent & momentum fluxes from urban canyon (roof, sunwall, shadewall, pervious & impervious road)

**`test/test_urban_fluxes.jl`** — Tests covering:
- Parameter struct defaults and read function
- `simple_wasteheatfromac` with all HAC modes (off, on, wasteheat_on)
- Full smoke test of `urban_fluxes!` with 5 urban columns (roof, sunwall, shadewall, road_imperv, road_perv)
- `calc_simple_internal_building_temp!` correctness
- Physical reasonableness checks (temperature bounds, wind stress sign, humidity range, zero wall evaporation, roots only on pervious road, etc.)

**All 8585 tests pass.**
